## Lane 6 Female Interleave. Anaconda is the package manager that will run this operation of combining the PE reads. Need to activate the khmer environment. This should change handle from "seboles@farm:~$" to "(khmer_env)seboles@farm:~$". Double check to see if dammit and split-paired-reads.py. Run all of these commands in the same directory that the sbatch command is located. 

```source ~/.bashrc```
```source activate khmer_env```
```pip install dammit```
```split-paired-reads.py```
```sbatch interleavelane6female2.sh```
##Here is the sbatch command. 

```#!/bin/bash -l
#SBATCH -J interleave_job
#SBATCH -t 12:00:00
#SBATCH -p high
#SBATCH --cpus-per-task=4

PROJECTROOT=/home/seboles/abaloneraw/DataLane6/RawLane6/FemaleLane6/TRIMFEMALELANE6/
INTERLEAVEDIR=/home/seboles/abaloneraw/DataLane6/RawLane6/FemaleLane6/interleave/
for filename in $PROJECTROOT/*_R1_*.qc.fq.gz
do
     # first, make the base by removing .extract.fastq.gz
     base=$(basename $filename .qc.fq.gz)
     echo $base

     # now, construct the R2 filename by replacing R1 with R2
     baseR2=${base/_R1_/_R2_}
     echo $baseR2
     
     # construct the output filename
     output=$INTERLEAVEDIR/${base/_R1/}.pe.qc.fq.gz
     echo output
     (interleave-reads.py $PROJECTROOT/${base}.qc.fq.gz $PROJECTROOT/${baseR2}.qc.fq.gz | gzip > $output)
done```
